  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; validation results carry full provenance. A central hemolysis acceptability claim is registered but its derivation from evidence is not formally linked — constituting a subtle epistemic gap (W-EP-01).",
